    "body": "After extensive testing, I've isolated the issue. This is not an issue with starship but with fish/vscode. When the ``fish_prompt`` function is set using source, it breaks the vscode shell integration. This is only true for the regular prompt and not the right prompt. I confirmed this by manually sourcing a file with the fish_prompt function defined. I also verified that this issue isn't a starship specific issue by removing the fish_prompt declaration from starship.fish and verifying that shell integration works. Closing this issue",
